What is Homology?
A topological invariant which assigns
a vector space, H
k
(X ), to a given
topological space X .
Dimension
k is the dimension
0: Clusters
1: Holes
2: Voids

Persistent Homology
What is Persistent Homology?
A way to watch how the homology of a ﬁltration (sequence) of topological spaces changes so
that we can understand something about the space.
Given topological space K and ﬁltration
